{
  "document_id": "ps-106",
  "title": "Psalms 106",
  "type": "scripture",
  "translation": "NRSVue",
  "blocks": [
    {
      "block_id": "ps-106-1",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 1,
      "text": "Praise the Lord!"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-106-2",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 2,
      "text": "Who can utter the mighty doings of the Lord"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-106-3",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 3,
      "text": "Happy are those who observe justice,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-106-4",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 4,
      "text": "Remember us, O Lord, when you show favor to your people;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-106-5",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 5,
      "text": "that we may see the prosperity of your chosen ones,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-106-6",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 6,
      "text": "Both we and our ancestors have sinned;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-106-7",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 7,
      "text": "Our ancestors, when they were in Egypt,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-106-8",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 8,
      "text": "Yet he saved them for his name’s sake,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-106-9",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 9,
      "text": "He rebuked the Red Sea, and it became dry;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-106-10",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 10,
      "text": "So he saved them from the hand of the foe"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-106-11",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 11,
      "text": "The waters covered their adversaries;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-106-12",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 12,
      "text": "Then they believed his words;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-106-13",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 13,
      "text": "But they soon forgot his works;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-106-14",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 14,
      "text": "But they had a wanton craving in the wilderness"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-106-15",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 15,
      "text": "he gave them what they asked"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-106-16",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 16,
      "text": "They were jealous of Moses in the camp"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-106-17",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 17,
      "text": "The earth opened and swallowed up Dathan"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-106-18",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 18,
      "text": "Fire also broke out in their company;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-106-19",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 19,
      "text": "They made a calf at Horeb"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-106-20",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 20,
      "text": "They exchanged the glory of God"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-106-21",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 21,
      "text": "They forgot God, their Savior,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-106-22",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 22,
      "text": "wondrous works in the land of Ham,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-106-23",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 23,
      "text": "Therefore he said he would destroy them—"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-106-24",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 24,
      "text": "Then they despised the pleasant land,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-106-25",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 25,
      "text": "They grumbled in their tents"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-106-26",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 26,
      "text": "Therefore he raised his hand and swore to them"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-106-27",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 27,
      "text": "and would disperse their descendants among the nations,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-106-28",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 28,
      "text": "Then they attached themselves to the Baal of Peor"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-106-29",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 29,
      "text": "they provoked the Lord to anger with their deeds,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-106-30",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 30,
      "text": "Then Phinehas stood up and interceded,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-106-31",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 31,
      "text": "And that has been reckoned to him as righteousness"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-106-32",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 32,
      "text": "They angered the Lord at the waters of Meribah,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-106-33",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 33,
      "text": "for they made his spirit bitter,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-106-34",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 34,
      "text": "They did not destroy the peoples,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-106-35",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 35,
      "text": "but they mingled with the nations"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-106-36",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 36,
      "text": "They served their idols,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-106-37",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 37,
      "text": "They sacrificed their sons"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-106-38",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 38,
      "text": "they poured out innocent blood,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-106-39",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 39,
      "text": "Thus they became unclean by their acts"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-106-40",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 40,
      "text": "Then the anger of the Lord was kindled against his people,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-106-41",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 41,
      "text": "he gave them into the hand of the nations,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-106-42",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 42,
      "text": "Their enemies oppressed them,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-106-43",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 43,
      "text": "Many times he delivered them,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-106-44",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 44,
      "text": "Nevertheless, he regarded their distress"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-106-45",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 45,
      "text": "For their sake he remembered his covenant"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-106-46",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 46,
      "text": "He caused them to be pitied"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-106-47",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 47,
      "text": "Save us, O Lord our God,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-106-48",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 48,
      "text": "Blessed be the Lord, the God of Israel,"
    }
  ]
}